R \sin\theta
R\,\text{d}\theta
\theta = 0
\theta = \frac\pi2
\int_{0}^{\frac\pi2} \text{d}A = 2 \int_{0}^{\frac\pi2} 2\pi R^2\sin\theta\text{d}\theta
A = 4\pi R^2 \int_{0}^{\frac\pi2}\sin\theta\text{d}\theta
A = 4\pi R^2 \left(-\cos\theta\Big|_{0}^{\frac\pi2}\right)
A = 4\pi R^2 (-\cos(\pi / 2) + \cos(0))
A = 4\pi R^2 (0 + 1)
A = 4\pi R^2
R
R\,\text{d}\theta
\theta = 0
\theta = \frac\pi2
\frac{\pi}{2} - 1
\int_{0}^{\frac\pi2} \text{d}A = 2 \int_{0}^{\frac\pi2} 2\pi R^2\,\text{d}\theta
A = 4\pi R^2 \int_{0}^{\frac\pi2}\text{d}\theta
A = 4\pi R^2 \left(\theta\Big|_{0}^{\frac\pi2}\right)
A = 4\pi R^2 (\pi / 2 - 0)
A = 4\pi R^2 (\pi / 2)
